This paper discusses the coexistence of Zigbee and IEEE 802.11b WLAN in a ubiquitous network environment, which involves topics related to network protocols, wireless communication, and system design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also discusses channel allocation and interference mitigation techniques, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions multimedia applications (cs.MM) and security issues (cs.CR), which are relevant sub-categories in computer science.
